---
/**
 * Home — "Swiss / editorial, mono-led" direction, three-track desktop layout.
 *
 * The desktop width is used by ADDING COLUMNS, not by widening the prose: the
 * reading column stays at a ~66-character measure (~40rem), and the recovered
 * horizontal space holds two margin rails —
 *   left:  a section index (sticky nav), and
 *   right: a persistent LIVE telemetry aside (the "this page monitors itself"
 *          thesis, given a permanent home: req/s + sparkline, targets, alerts,
 *          build, and the latest homelab commit).
 * On narrow screens it collapses to one column (live panel as a band, index
 * hidden). See ~/Projects/portfolio-design-research.md, Part 5.
 *
 * Type rule: SERIF for human content (name, project titles, prose); MONO for
 * everything systemic (labels, numbers, nav, live data). Zero radius, hairline
 * rules, no shadows, one reserved accent. Live wiring is the external module
 * public/home.js so the CSP stays inline-free.
 */
---

<div class="home">
  <header class="masthead">
    <div class="masthead__id">
      <p class="eyebrow">Platform · DevOps · SRE</p>
      <h1 class="name">Henry Dowd</h1>
      <p class="tagline">I build infrastructure and the things that run on it — plus the odd Android app.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="masthead__side">
      <p class="badge" aria-live="polite">
        <span class="live__dot" data-dot="cluster" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        homelab · <span data-live-state>connecting…</span>
      </p>
      <nav class="contact" aria-label="Contact and links">
        <a class="contact__row" href="mailto:henry@dowd.ie"><span class="contact__k">Email</span><span class="contact__v">henry@dowd.ie</span></a>
        <a class="contact__row" href="https://github.com/hpdowd" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span class="contact__k">GitHub</span><span class="contact__v">github.com/hpdowd</span></a>
        <a class="contact__row" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/henrypdowd/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span class="contact__k">LinkedIn</span><span class="contact__v">in/henrypdowd</span></a>
        <a class="contact__row" href="/cv/"><span class="contact__k">CV</span><span class="contact__v">the full CV →</span></a>
        <a class="contact__row" href="/about/"><span class="contact__k">About</span><span class="contact__v">more about me →</span></a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <hr class="rule" />

  <div class="grid">
    <nav class="rail" aria-label="Sections">
      <ol class="index">
        <li><a href="#intro">About</a></li>
        <li><a href="#work">Projects</a></li>
        <li><a href="#approach">Skills</a></li>
      </ol>
      <p class="rail__note">Self-hosted on k3s.<br />This page runs on the same<br />platform it reports on.</p>
    </nav>

    <main class="body">
      <section id="intro" class="block">
        <h2 class="block__h">About</h2>
        <p class="lede">
          I build software and then run it myself, on hardware I own. Most of it
          lands on a small Kubernetes cluster at home — the same cluster that
          serves this page and feeds the panel on the right. I'm drawn to the
          unglamorous parts: deploys that don't wake you up, and monitoring that
          notices a problem before a user does.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="work" class="block">
        <h2 class="block__h">Projects</h2>

        <article class="entry">
          <div class="entry__head">
            <h3><a href="https://github.com/hpdowd/homelab" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Homelab platform</a></h3>
            <p class="entry__meta">k3s · ArgoCD · VictoriaMetrics · Gitea</p>
          </div>
          <p>
            A Kubernetes cluster I run at home on Proxmox. It's all GitOps: I push
            to my own Gitea, ArgoCD brings the cluster in line with the repo, and
            VictoriaMetrics keeps an eye on the rest. It hosts Nextcloud, Immich
            and a handful of other things — including this page, which gets scraped
            by the same stack that's filling the panel on the right.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="entry">
          <div class="entry__head">
            <h3><a href="https://github.com/hpdowd/paraphrase_detector" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Paraphrase detector</a></h3>
            <p class="entry__meta">Python · scikit-learn · Sentence-BERT · final-year project</p>
          </div>
          <p>
            Works out whether two sentences mean the same thing. Instead of
            fine-tuning a big model and treating it as a black box, I combined four
            features you can actually inspect — BERT similarity, tree-edit distance
            over the parse, word overlap and a length ratio — into a logistic
            regression. On the MSR Paraphrase Corpus it edged out BERT on its own
            (0.79 ROC AUC against 0.78), and each of the four features held up as
            a significant signal in its own right.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="entry">
          <div class="entry__head">
            <h3><a href="https://github.com/hpdowd/nextkeep" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NextKeep</a></h3>
            <p class="entry__meta">Android · Kotlin · Jetpack Compose</p>
          </div>
          <p>
            A notes app for Android that syncs with a self-hosted Nextcloud Notes
            server — the feel of Google Keep, without Google keeping the notes.
            Everything lives in a local Room database first and syncs over Retrofit
            when there's a connection, so it still works on the train. QR-code
            login, a markdown editor, dynamic theming.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="entry">
          <div class="entry__head">
            <h3><a href="https://github.com/hpdowd/PDF-Sorter" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PDF-Sorter</a></h3>
            <p class="entry__meta">Python · Tesseract OCR</p>
          </div>
          <p>
            A desktop tool that files PDFs by what's inside them rather than what
            they're named. It reads the text, falls back to OCR on scans, and sorts
            against rules you set. I wrote it for the moment you're staring down a
            few hundred invoices with no patience left; it ships as one Windows
            installer with Tesseract bundled in.
          </p>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section id="approach" class="block">
        <h2 class="block__h">Skills</h2>
        <dl class="skills">
          <div><dt>Containers &amp; GitOps</dt><dd>Kubernetes · ArgoCD · Helm · Sealed Secrets</dd></div>
          <div><dt>Linux &amp; networking</dt><dd>Arch Linux · Proxmox · WireGuard · split-horizon DNS</dd></div>
          <div><dt>Observability</dt><dd>VictoriaMetrics · Grafana · Alertmanager · restic</dd></div>
          <div><dt>Languages</dt><dd>Python · Java · C · Bash · SQL</dd></div>
        </dl>
      </section>

    </main>

    <aside class="aside" aria-label="Live homelab telemetry">
      <div class="readout">
        <p class="readout__head">
          <span class="live__dot" data-dot="cluster" aria-hidden="true"></span> live · self-monitored
        </p>
        <dl class="metrics">
          <div class="metric metric--lead">
            <dt>req/s · this service</dt>
            <dd>
              <span data-rate>—</span>
              <svg class="spark" data-spark viewBox="0 0 120 26" preserveAspectRatio="none" aria-hidden="true">
                <polyline class="spark__line" fill="none" points="" />
              </svg>
            </dd>
          </div>
          <div class="metric"><dt>targets up</dt><dd data-targets>—</dd></div>
          <div class="metric"><dt>alerts firing</dt><dd data-alerts>—</dd></div>
          <div class="metric"><dt>running build</dt><dd data-build>—</dd></div>
        </dl>
      </div>
      <div class="latest">
        <p class="readout__head">latest change</p>
        <p class="latest__body" data-latest>—</p>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Live wiring is a same-origin external module so the CSP stays script-src 'self'. -->
<script type="module" src="/home.js"></script>

<style>
  .home {
    --rule: var(--line);
    color: var(--ink);
  }

  /* ---- Masthead ---- */
  .masthead {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem 2rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.74rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem;
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.55rem;
  }
  .eyebrow::before { content: ""; width: 1.6rem; height: 2px; background: var(--accent); flex: none; }
  .name {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: clamp(3.2rem, 9vw, 5.6rem);
    line-height: 0.94;
    letter-spacing: -0.022em;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .tagline {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2.4vw, 1.5rem);
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0.7rem 0 0;
    max-width: 26rem;
  }
  .badge {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0.4rem 0 0;
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;
  }
  .live__dot { width: 9px; height: 9px; background: var(--ink-soft); flex: none; }
  .live__dot.is-ok { background: var(--ok); animation: home-pulse 2.6s ease-in-out infinite; }
  .live__dot.is-warn { background: var(--warn); }
  .live__dot.is-err { background: var(--err); }
  @keyframes home-pulse { 0%, 100% { opacity: 1; } 50% { opacity: 0.35; } }

  .rule { border: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); margin: 1.5rem 0 0; }

  /* ---- Three-track grid (collapses to one column) ---- */
  .grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    grid-template-areas: "body" "aside";
    gap: 2rem;
    padding-top: 1.25rem;
  }
  .rail { grid-area: rail; display: none; font-family: var(--mono); align-self: start; }
  .body { grid-area: body; max-width: 40rem; }
  .aside { grid-area: aside; align-self: start; }

  @media (min-width: 66rem) {
    .grid {
      grid-template-columns: 11rem minmax(0, 1fr) 15rem;
      grid-template-areas: "rail body aside";
      gap: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.5rem);
    }
    .rail { display: block; position: sticky; top: 1.5rem; }
    .aside { position: sticky; top: 1.5rem; }
  }

  /* ---- Left rail: section index ---- */
  .index { list-style: none; margin: 0 0 1.75rem; padding: 0; }
  .index li { padding: 0.5rem 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .index li:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .index a { color: var(--ink); text-decoration: none; transition: color 0.15s ease; }
  .index a:hover { color: var(--accent); }
  .index a.is-active { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; }
  .rail__note { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--ink-soft); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0; }

  /* ---- Reading column ---- */
  .block { padding: 2.75rem 0; }
  .block:first-child { padding-top: 0; }
  .block + .block { border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .block__h {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem; font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .lede { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 2.9vw, 1.85rem); line-height: 1.45; margin: 0; color: var(--ink); }

  .entry { padding: 1.6rem 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .entry:first-of-type { border-top: 0; padding-top: 0.25rem; }
  .entry__head { margin-bottom: 0.7rem; }
  .entry h3 { font-family: var(--serif); font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.5rem; line-height: 1.15; letter-spacing: -0.01em; margin: 0; }
  .entry h3 a { color: var(--ink); text-decoration: none; }
  .entry h3 a:hover { color: var(--accent); }
  .entry h3 a[target="_blank"]::after { content: " ↗"; color: var(--ink-soft); font-size: 0.7em; }
  .entry__meta { font-family: var(--serif); font-style: italic; font-size: 0.98rem; color: var(--accent); margin: 0.4rem 0 0; }
  .entry p { font-family: var(--sans); font-size: 1.02rem; line-height: 1.6; margin: 0; color: var(--ink); }

  .skills { margin: 0; }
  .skills div { display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 9rem) 1fr; gap: 0.5rem 1.5rem; padding: 0.65rem 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .skills div:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .skills dt { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.78rem; letter-spacing: 0.04em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-soft); margin: 0; }
  .skills dd { margin: 0; font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.95rem; }

  .masthead__side { min-width: 15rem; }
  .contact { margin: 1.1rem 0 0; }
  .contact__row {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 5rem 1fr; gap: 0.9rem; align-items: baseline;
    padding: 0.5rem 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); text-decoration: none;
  }
  .contact__row:last-child { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule); }
  .contact__k { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.65rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-soft); }
  .contact__v { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--ink); }
  .contact__row:hover .contact__v { color: var(--accent); }
  .home a:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid var(--accent); outline-offset: 3px; }

  /* ---- Right aside: live telemetry ---- */
  .readout { border-top: 2px solid var(--accent); padding-top: 0.8rem; }
  .readout__head {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.72rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 0.85rem; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;
  }
  .metrics { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(6rem, 1fr)); gap: 0.75rem 1.5rem; margin: 0; }
  .metric dt { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.66rem; letter-spacing: 0.05em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-soft); margin: 0 0 0.2rem; }
  .metric dd { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 1.3rem; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; margin: 0; line-height: 1.05; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.55rem; }
  .metric--lead dd { font-size: 1.75rem; }
  .spark { width: 64px; height: 20px; flex: none; }
  .spark__line { stroke: var(--accent); stroke-width: 1.5; vector-effect: non-scaling-stroke; }

  .latest { margin-top: 1.5rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); padding-top: 0.9rem; }
  .latest__body { font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 0.82rem; line-height: 1.55; color: var(--ink); margin: 0; }

  @media (min-width: 66rem) {
    /* In the narrow aside column, stack the metrics as hairline-ruled rows. */
    .metrics { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0; }
    .metric { border-top: 1px solid var(--rule); padding: 0.6rem 0; }
    .metric--lead { border-top: 0; padding-top: 0; }
    .metric dd { justify-content: space-between; }
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .live__dot.is-ok { animation: none; }
    .index a { transition: none; }
  }
</style>
